race.comment: Scratchings leave this a wide open event. EPIC PROPORTIONS (9) is racing well, winning strongly from the front two back before a 1.4L defeat over the 1200m at Eagle Farm just last week. On the quick turnaround today, but seems to have taken to QLD beautifully and rates highly as he drops down in weight. Expecting him to roll across and use the light weight to his advantage. MIDNIGHT IN TOKYO (8) is first-up today following an impressive trial win at Deagon in a strong heat. She too is down in the weights today and gets leading rider Ben Thompson in the saddle. Maps to get every chance and she's a fresh winner in the past. She's the main danger. HATCHET (12) finished behind EPIC PROPORTIONS 21 days ago when beaten 2.1L, but he meets that galloper on better terms today. Can make his presence felt with a touch of luck from the draw.  ROCKRIBBED (3) will be screwed down tight for this after three trials coming in and he boasts a strong fresh record. Key player.
